The paper deals with the problem of minimizing delay in decentralized wireless networks using network coding. This involves cooperative data exchange and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with wireless networks, which suggests the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Game theory is a key tool used in the paper, which suggests the sub-category cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also deals with collective behavior and system performance, which suggests the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with decentralized systems, which suggests the sub-category cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
